OL,3,CLiam Payne: The boy from Bushbury who
OL,4,Cbecame a global sensation
OL,6,FThe next time I met Liam was backstage
OL,7,Fduring one of the knock-out rounds (I
OL,8,Fwas actually there as a personal guest
OL,9,Fof Wagner, but that's a story for
OL,10,Fanother time).
OL,12,F"I'm sure you don't remember me, but I
OL,13,Fsaw you at the Dudley Christmas lights
OL,14,Fthing last year," I said, having
OL,15,Fhunted him down through the crowds
OL,16,Fmilling around at the afterparty. "Can
OL,17,Fyou believe how far you've come?"
OL,19,FHe laughed. "It's all a bit of a blur
OL,20,F- it's like a dream. I just hope it's
OL,21,Fnot over yet."
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/12
